sentations of Green's functions, includes all the standard Green's functions and many novel ones, and provides innovative and new approaches that might lead to Green's functions. The book is a useful source for everyone who is studying or working in the fields of science, finance, or engineering that involve practical solution of partial differential equations.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aGreen's functions. 4aElliptisch. 4aGreensche Funktion. 4aParabolisch. 4aPartielle Differenzialgleichung. 7aMATHEMATICS / Differential Equations / General.2bisacsh  aElliptic.  aGreen's Function.  aParabolic.  aPartial Differential Equation.1 aMelnikov, Max Y., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Studies in Mathematics eBook-Packagez9783110494938oZDB-23-GSM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Mathematics 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023847108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Mathematics - 2000 - 2014z9783110637205oZDB-23-GMA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE MATHEMATICS, PHYSICS, ENGINEERING 2012z9783110293722oZDB-23-DMI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET MATHEMATIK, PHYSIK, INGENIEURWISS. 2012z9783110288926oZDB-23-DMP0 cprintz978311025302340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311025339940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110253399423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110253399/original  a978-3-11-023847-1  DGBA Backlist Mathematics 2000-2014 (EN)c20